text: Tudor Dixon (n√©e Makary, born May 5, 1977) is an American politician, conservative commentator and actress. She was the Republican party's nominee for Governor of Michigan in the 2022 election. After Joe Biden's victory in the 2020 election, Dixon supported Donald Trump's false claim that he actually won the election and his efforts to overturn the election results. ==References== Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:American political commentators Category:Actors from Michigan Category:Politicians from Michigan Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
